<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-85-0292 </DOCNO><TEXT>The world's population is increasing and it will not be possible to multiplypresent patterns of energy supply to serve an expected world economy5 to 10 times as large as the present one. A safe and environmentallysound energy programme that will sustain human progress into the futureis needed. This requires new dimensions of political will and internationalcooperation. The Norwegian approach to the energy situation is stated.Its policy on oil is that Norway should contribute to stabilize the internationaloil market at a reasonably high price level. This it is doing by reducinggrowth in crude oil production. Norway's natural gas reserves are suchthat substantial increase in sales would be possible.</TEXT></DOC>